1
00:00:00,590 --> 00:00:07,130
Hello, my name is Emma, and in today's video,
I'm going to teach you a simple grammar point,

2
00:00:07,130 --> 00:00:11,460
and that is how we can use infinitives to
give a reason for something.

3
00:00:11,460 --> 00:00:12,460
Okay?

4
00:00:12,460 --> 00:00:16,730
So, in this video, I'm going to teach you
what an infinitive is and how we use it in

5
00:00:16,730 --> 00:00:17,730
this way.

6
00:00:17,730 --> 00:00:20,020
So, let's get started.

7
00:00:20,020 --> 00:00:28,740
So, like I said, we use an infinitive verb
to say why someone does something.

8
00:00:28,740 --> 00:00:32,800
So, let's look at some examples.

9
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:36,640
I took a shower - why?

10
00:00:36,640 --> 00:00:38,840
To relax.

11
00:00:38,840 --> 00:00:41,530
I worked - why?

12
00:00:41,530 --> 00:00:42,579
What's the reason?

13
00:00:42,579 --> 00:00:44,910
I worked to make money.

14
00:00:44,910 --> 00:00:45,910
Okay?

15
00:00:45,910 --> 00:00:52,190
So, what I'm doing here is I'm showing you
part of a sentence and then, at the end, is

16
00:00:52,190 --> 00:00:55,110
an infinitive verb that shows the reason why.

17
00:00:55,110 --> 00:01:04,180
So, an infinitive is when you have the preposition
"to" + the base verb.

18
00:01:04,180 --> 00:01:05,570
So, what's the base verb?

19
00:01:05,570 --> 00:01:12,729
It means it's a verb that's not conjugated,
it's not in any tense, so for example, "to

20
00:01:12,729 --> 00:01:15,969
be" is an infinitive verb.

21
00:01:15,969 --> 00:01:22,840
Are, is, was, those are not the infinitive
verb, "to be" is the infinitive verb.

22
00:01:22,840 --> 00:01:25,659
I have some other examples here.

23
00:01:25,659 --> 00:01:35,060
"To eat", "to make", "to do", so an infinitive
verb is the verb before you conjugate it,

24
00:01:35,060 --> 00:01:38,179
and again, it has that preposition "to".

25
00:01:38,179 --> 00:01:43,759
So, I want you to tell me, what is the infinitive
verb in our first example?

26
00:01:43,759 --> 00:01:47,289
"I took a shower to relax."

27
00:01:47,289 --> 00:01:53,959
So, the infinitive verb is "to relax".

28
00:01:53,959 --> 00:01:57,489
What about in our second example?

29
00:01:57,489 --> 00:02:01,770
"I worked to make money."

30
00:02:01,770 --> 00:02:04,889
If you said "to make" is the infinitive, you're
correct.

31
00:02:04,889 --> 00:02:09,709
I know I put a box around it so it might seem
a little simple, but those are examples of

32
00:02:09,709 --> 00:02:10,799
infinitive verbs.

33
00:02:10,799 --> 00:02:17,090
So, again, we use infinitive verbs to give
the reason why we do something.

34
00:02:17,090 --> 00:02:19,569
So now, let's look at some more examples.

35
00:02:19,569 --> 00:02:22,480
Okay, so let's look at another example.

36
00:02:22,480 --> 00:02:26,430
She came, why did she come?

37
00:02:26,430 --> 00:02:31,319
Well, one example might be, "She came to dance."

38
00:02:31,319 --> 00:02:35,310
"She came to see friends."

39
00:02:35,310 --> 00:02:40,659
She came to meet people.

40
00:02:40,659 --> 00:02:45,939
So notice we have "to" which is the preposition
of an infinitive, and then we have the verb,

41
00:02:45,939 --> 00:02:52,909
in this case we can add "meet".

42
00:02:52,909 --> 00:02:58,359
Can you think of an example using a verb to
answer why she came?

43
00:02:58,359 --> 00:03:03,060
I know there's not a lot of information, so
there's a lot of different answers you could

44
00:03:03,060 --> 00:03:05,080
say.

45
00:03:05,080 --> 00:03:07,840
Let's look at some other examples.

46
00:03:07,840 --> 00:03:14,999
I want you to think about the reason: Why
do you go to the library?

47
00:03:14,999 --> 00:03:22,230
Some people might say "You go to the library
to read."

48
00:03:22,230 --> 00:03:27,379
Now, I want you to think, what part of the
sentence is the infinitive?

49
00:03:27,379 --> 00:03:30,590
That is the part that is giving the reason.

50
00:03:30,590 --> 00:03:39,969
What we have here, the preposition "to" and
the base verb "read", so "to read" is the

51
00:03:39,969 --> 00:03:42,030
infinitive.

52
00:03:42,030 --> 00:03:44,819
And that's also the reason why we go to the
library.

53
00:03:44,819 --> 00:03:47,890
Now, I want you to think about the cinema.

54
00:03:47,890 --> 00:03:51,390
Why do you go to the cinema, what's the reason?

55
00:03:51,390 --> 00:03:56,800
You go to the cinema maybe to watch movies.

56
00:03:56,800 --> 00:04:00,450
So, what part is the infinitive verb in this?

57
00:04:00,450 --> 00:04:10,689
So again, we have the preposition "to" and
the base verb, which is "watch".

58
00:04:10,689 --> 00:04:13,569
This is the infinitive.

59
00:04:13,569 --> 00:04:18,228
You go to the cinema to watch movies.

60
00:04:18,228 --> 00:04:23,310
Let's look at another example: why do you
go to the gym?

61
00:04:23,310 --> 00:04:30,250
Some of you might say you go to the gym to
work out, or to get strong.

62
00:04:30,250 --> 00:04:34,039
What's another reason why you might go to
the gym?

63
00:04:34,039 --> 00:04:41,830
Maybe to check people out, I don't know, there's
a lot of reasons why you might go to the gym.

64
00:04:41,830 --> 00:04:44,450
Maybe you want to train, okay?

65
00:04:44,450 --> 00:04:46,830
So, this is just one example.

66
00:04:46,830 --> 00:04:50,410
You go to the gym, and what part is the infinitive?

67
00:04:50,410 --> 00:04:56,919
Well again, you need the preposition "to",
in this case "work out" is the verb.

68
00:04:56,919 --> 00:05:03,750
Okay, now I want you to imagine this: your
grandmother or grandfather or somebody you

69
00:05:03,750 --> 00:05:10,180
know has never used the internet before, and
they want to know more about the internet,

70
00:05:10,180 --> 00:05:14,720
and so they ask you "Why do you use YouTube?"

71
00:05:14,720 --> 00:05:16,340
What can you tell them?

72
00:05:16,340 --> 00:05:31,500
Well, one example might be "You use you YouTube
to", so we have the infinitive, maybe "study

73
00:05:31,500 --> 00:05:36,760
English".

74
00:05:36,760 --> 00:05:41,319
I use YouTube to watch cat videos.

75
00:05:41,319 --> 00:05:42,599
Okay?

76
00:05:42,599 --> 00:05:47,150
I use YouTube to watch old TV shows.

77
00:05:47,150 --> 00:05:52,290
So, you can think about the reasons why you
do something and, again, you use the preposition

78
00:05:52,290 --> 00:05:55,780
"to" and the base verb.

79
00:05:55,780 --> 00:05:56,780
What about Tinder?

80
00:05:56,780 --> 00:06:03,449
I don't know if people are still using Tinder,
but if they are, if you know what Tinder is,

81
00:06:03,449 --> 00:06:07,840
why would you use Tinder?

82
